data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10, you could opt in to sync-over-async; in .NET 11 that opt-in is gone. Calling any synchronous API (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throws** — no workaround.

### Fix: convert everything to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through your call chain — callers must also become `async`/`await` up to the controller level (ASP.NET Core controllers already support `Task<T>` returns). Remove any sync-over-async opt-in configuration you had in .NET 10, as it's now a no-op.
